<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-08-30T14:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-08-30T14:42:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.85/42: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-30T15:00:00-04:42"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1927—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>115. Government has sent to Congress project of law embodying all points
                            of my 111, August 25, 4 p.m., except point 2. Omission of latter will
                            probably greatly diminish opposition to bill by British shipowners and
                            eliminate that of other nations. Grace Line is seriously and almost
                            solely threatened. I renew request for instructions by cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Collier</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>